1. Theoretical models                                             7040 1451
 The POD code is based on the spherical optical model, the        7040 1451
distorted-wave Born approximaiton (DWBA), one-component exciton   7040 1451
preequilibrium model, and the Hauser-Feshbach-Moldauer statis-    7040 1451
tical model.  With the preequilibrium model, semi-empirical       7040 1451
pickup and knockout process can be taken into account for         7040 1451
composite-particle emission.  The gamma-ray emission from the     7040 1451
compound nucleus can be calculated within the framework of the    7040 1451
exciton model.  The code is capable of reading in particle        7040 1451
transmission coefficients calculated by separate spherical or     7040 1451
coupled-channel optical model code. In this evaluation, the OPTMAN7040 1451
/4/ code was employed for neutrons, while the ECIS code           7040 1451
/6/ was adopted for charged particles.                            7040 1451
